The paper focuses on the development and evaluation of a privacy game for wearable devices, specifically smartwatches. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which deals with the design, evaluation, and use of interactive computing systems for human use. Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and privacy (cs.CR), which are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves data analysis and visualization (cs.SI) and game design (cs.GR), which are relevant sub-categories given the methodology and focus of the study.
